  "prompt": "What social media platforms are best to use for a restaurant and how often should someone post?",
  "response": "For a restaurant, the best social media platforms to use are Instagram, Facebook, and X (formerly Twitter). Here's a brief overview of each platform and how often you should post:\n\n1. Instagram:\n   - Ideal for showcasing visually appealing food, drinks, and ambiance.\n   - Use Instagram Stories and Reels to engage with your audience.\n   - Post frequency: 3-5 times per week.\n\n2. Facebook:\n   - Great for sharing updates, events, and promotions.\n   - Useful for targeting local customers with ads.\n   - Post frequency: 2-3 times per week.\n\n3. X (formerly Twitter):\n   - Excellent for real-time updates, daily specials, and customer interactions.\n   - Use hashtags to increase visibility and reach.\n   - Post frequency: 1-2 times per day.\n\nAdditionally, consider using other platforms like Yelp and Google My Business to manage your online presence and respond to customer reviews.\n\nRemember to maintain a consistent posting schedule and engage with your audience to build a strong online presence for your restaurant.",
